unavailability_reason:
Trading capacity calculated according to Capacity calculation methodology for the day-ahead and intraday market timeframes within the Baltic CCR (https://umm.nordpoolgroup.com/#/messages/5682698e-855c-4430-91f9-db0b91a14bf7/1).
PL-LT interconnection lines Alytus-Elk Bis 1 and Alytus-Elk Bis 2 will be in normal operation. They are indicated as Assets due to the mandatory requirement to indicate asset elements while publishing UMMs.
remarks: LT-PL cross border installed capacity calculated based on frequency stability criteria in order to ensure Baltic states power systems frequency stability in case of unplanned disconnection from CESA.

unavailability_reason:
During Baltic PS’s synchronous operation with continental Europe PS’s according to preliminary evaluation LT-PL connection capacity will be 150 MW in both directions. Capacity calculated based on the proposal of Baltic CCR TSOs’ Common Capacities Calculation Methodology for LT Time Frames.
PL-LT interconnection lines Alytus-Elk Bis 1 and Alytus-Elk Bis 2 will be in normal operation. They are indicated as Assets due to the mandatory requirement to indicate asset elements while publishing UMMs.
remarks: Installed capacity is increased due to evaluation of additional measures to ensure frequency stability in Baltic states power systems. LT-PL cross border installed capacity calculated based on frequency stability criteria in order to ensure Baltic states power systems frequency stability after unplanned disconnection from Continental Europe synchronous area.

unavailability_reason: Change of dimensioning fault in Finland.
remarks: The maximum net transfer capacity (NTC) from Sweden (SE1) to Finland (FI) is dependent on the dimensioning fault in Finland. When dimensioning fault is 1000 MW or more, the NTC from SE1 to FI is maximum 1200 MW. When dimensioning fault is less than 1000 MW, the NTC from SE1 to FI is maximum 1500 MW. For more information: https://www.fingrid.fi/en/news/news/2022/impact-of-olkiluoto-3-on-transmission-capacity-given-to-electricity-market-between-finland-and-sweden-on-northern-interconnections.

The expected start of commercial operation is February 2027.

remarks: The Nordic TSOs acknowledge that our current tool for estimating the impact on cross-zonal exchange, as required by TR (EU Regulation 543/2013), is not yet optimized for the flow-based capacity calculation process. We are actively working on improving this tool.
Due to planned disconnection of S 300 Modalen- Steinsland and S 300 Steinsland-Haugsvær, the production from Steinsland will be confined with the entire capacity of 170 MW.
Disconnection of 300kV Børtveit-Midtfjellet. Midtfjellet wind power plant will be able to supply the local grid with a maximum of 30 MW. That means approximately 120 MW will be unavailable.
Due to disconnection of Steinsland-Modalen during both disconnection and connection Steinsland-Haugsvær, Steinsland will be isolated from the grid with 170 MW.
